The paper deals with the problem of reaching agreement between rational agents, which is a central topic in game theory (cs.GT). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in its analysis of the number of bits needed for agents to reach agreement. The use of protocols and simulations to achieve agreement suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves computational complexity (cs.DS) in its analysis of the efficiency of the protocols. Finally, the paper involves machine learning (cs.LG) in its use of Bayesian agents.
